So sick! Was not prepared to be on top of the boulder for the first time, but it was okay.

Potential new one right of Smackdown in Boulder Basin. Same jump-start, but immediately go right and up on small crimps and grainy slopers. Felt a bit harder than Smackdown. Felt impossible with tape so had to sacrifice the tips!

ascents.sectorName: Cabin Fever / The Perimeter / The Death Scream Area

ascents.comment: Underrated boulder, but holy shit that felt hard. Totally underestimated it.
Started on the mega jug and immediately went right before rejoining the main Jarash edge/plate thingy. Climbed well after the initial but-draggery. Probably been done.
Did the move without cutting to the jug. Reachy my way.
Started on the gaston as per Kaya description. Either way, pretty fun. Topped out direct and found that the huge jug isn't choss.
Tricky first move to a nearly one-move-wonder. Still quality.

Potential new one that starts on the good slot right of Cosmos (used to link into Cosmos for NDT v11) and climbs straight up using anything in reach. I didn't realize that the standard Champagne Supernova beta used all these holds, so this line stood out as obvious when viewing from the Cosmos side of the boulder. Might not be an FA or new line, but still really fun and fully utilizes the smile-shaped slot.
Sick board-style moves on very un-board-style holds!
First go after doing PFO. Climbs super well despite being a little squished up next to the v6.
Perfect holds on great rock!

Near the top of the talus field above Party of One - on the backside of a block with an obvious roof. Slightly dabby start from a nice crescent and downpull edge with the crux right below the lip. Might clean up to have more options. Great setting for a pretty cool boulder. 1-2 with Derek!
Cool sequences on this one! This variation makes great use out of so many holds.
Definitely didn't top out fully direct into the slab - ended up using the big sidepull out left after doing the first mantle.
Climbs really well!
Felt super improbable at first, but finding the right foothold made all the difference.

Hard! Tried a few times with the guidebook-approved method (deadpoint the sloped shelf from the jug-ledge), but couldn't stick well enough to pull through. Used a left crimp that was easily in reach to shorten the move. Definitely easier than the suggested beta, but that method felt like v8 to me.
Gaston pinch lock-off for the move to the block, then a weird flip grip to do the hop to the jug. So good, this place is stacked with quality.
That's a nice boulder.

Scoped this thing last trip and had to come back to scrub it up. I think it's as good as I hoped! Great send train with the homies. Slightly dabby start to a slightly spicy end crux with a couple different methods.

First go after doing the better line. Starts with a left downpulling edge and a nice right sidepull-edge directly under the topout of Making Friends. I jumped to the shelf, but you could probably also swing a heel. Not as good as the full line, but still nice.

Great find by Kody, great session with the crew. Really cool crimps through a nice overhang and a droppable press to finish it off. Hard to grade since it doesn't feel comparable to most of the 7c/+ I've tried in Kings, but consensus says 10 points and it's definitely the most my-style thing around.

Another KS brainchild. Squeezed it in last minute before heading home. Climbs the perfect crescent rails facing the Kombucha Cider boulder. Cuts left through the hallway to some crystal grips, then up through the good, but dirty rails. High, but manageable finish. 5 stars if not for the dab potential.
Blew the flash going for the first crimp! Fun little roof - reminded me of Yos or Kings rock.
First boulder in Tahoe! Sorry Seb, didn't earn the flash beer. Holy shit Pimp Slap is hard.
First go after Wick's - same funky top beta that apparently no one else does. Sick ass boulder. Holy grade consensus.
Almost went first go after the mid-start. Turns out we used unorthodox beta. Great climb!
Weird start. Cool climb.
Definitely felt like c+ after all the mileage that day. Hard to be sure. Gave up on sit starting from a pad stack.
Triple double with the friends!!! Can see this being way harder without the reach.
Heinous 3rd day on in the direct sun. Sick boulder, though!
